&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>gcloud auth application-default login
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Set your default Google Cloud project (replace &lt;code>YOUR_PROJECT_ID&lt;/code> with your actual project ID):
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>gcloud config set project YOUR_PROJECT_ID
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>export GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>YOUR_PROJECT_ID
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>Toolbox and the client libraries will use this project for BigQuery, unless overridden in configurations.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/quickstarts/query-public-dataset-console#before-you-begin">Enabled the BigQuery API&lt;/a> in your Google Cloud project.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Installed the BigQuery client library for Python:
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>pip install google-cloud-bigquery
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;/li>
